    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9600 AND 9700 SLEEPER AND NON-SLEEPER CABS -
        WINDSHIELD WIPERS (AIR)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>WINDSHIELD WIPERS (AIR)</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
            <para>The windshield wipers are driven by dual air powered wiper motors mounted below the windshield on the
                cab cowl bar. Wiper arms are attached directly to the motors, eliminating the need for mechanical
                linkage between the wipers. Each wiper is controlled by its own control valve located on the instrument
                console (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600676">Figure 76</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600676" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600676" filename="../figg16/g1600676.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 76. Location of Wiper and Washer Controls</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. WASHER CONTROL BUTTON</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. WIPER CONTROL KNOBS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
